<p><b>Token ring</b> <a href="/wiki/Local_area_network" title="Local area network">local area network</a> (LAN) technology is a local area network <a href="/wiki/Network_protocol" title="Network protocol" class="mw-redirect">protocol</a> which resides at the <a href="/wiki/Data_link_layer" title="Data link layer" class="mw-redirect">data link layer</a> (DLL) of the <a href="/wiki/OSI_model" title="OSI model">OSI model</a>. It uses a special three-byte frame called a token that travels around the ring. Token ring frames travel completely around the loop.</p>
